#: src-ru/data/events.xml.rawclobber:44964
msgid "data/events.xml.rawclobber$//event[@name=\"EVENT_ZOLTAN_CODEX_2\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"#RECORD-155. The Great Zoltan Wartime Code.\n"
"#155.1.1. The Supreme Commander of the Zoltan Fleet is the supreme authority.\n"
"#155.1.2. Orders of the Supreme Commander are to be carried out immediately, and their statements are accepted as absolute truth.\n"
"#155.1.3. Any living organism resisting the will of the Supreme Commander is subject to forced subjugation.\n"
"#155.1.3a. If subjugation is impossible, the organism is to be liquidated.\n"
"#155.2.1. Slave trading is forbidden in Zoltan sectors (trading sentient beings against their will).\n"
"#155.2.1a. The slave trading ban is lifted in critical wartime.\n"
"#155.3.1. All planetary colonization other than colonization by Zoltans is forbidden.\n"
"#155.4.1. Any terraforming operations are forbidden without consent from all residents of the planet.\n"
"#155.4.2. In case of disagreement by less than 1% of the population, forced relocation is permitted.\n"
"#155.5.1. Upon declaration of martial law, every armed Zoltan ship must report to the Zoltan fleet for further instructions.\n"
"#155.6.1. The decision to declare martial law (critical or standard) is made by the Zoltan council.\n"
"#155.6.2. Council members must number at least 200. A 100% consensus is required.\n"
"#155.7.1. Every Zoltan citizen has the right to self-determination, productive labor, support, and respect from Zoltan society.\n"
"#155.8.1. Every Zoltan citizen must comply with all codes and regulations.\n"
"#155.9.1. No being of another race may become a citizen of Zoltan society.\n"
"#155.9.1a. The Supreme Commander may grant 'citizen' status to a being of another race.\n"
"#155.10.1. A Zoltan citizen may freely leave and return to civilian sectors, provided they report their journey and events.\n"
"#155.11.1. Extraction of materials and resources in Zoltan sectors is permitted only with a license.\n"
"#155.11.2. Any materials obtained in Zoltan sectors without a license are subject to seizure with a fine of double the value of the materials.\n"
"#155.12.1. Listening to or storing the 'Great Zoltan Wartime Code' is permitted only in the presence of a Zoltan representative.\n"
"#155.12.2. Copying or distorting information in this code is forbidden.\n"
"#155.13.1. Upon meeting an enemy invader, any Zoltan ship must conduct a standard clearing procedure.\n"
"#155.13.2. Equipment obtained during clearing must be delivered to the Head of the Zoltan Fleet.\n"
"#155.13.3. If clearing is impossible, a tactical retreat is permitted, followed by reporting to the Head of the Zoltan Fleet.\n"
"#155.14.1. All transit transport operations through Zoltan sectors are subject to inspection.\n"
"#155.14.2. Refusal of inspection equates the ship to a hostile invader.\n"
"#155.14.3. During inspection, any equipment on the prohibited technology list may be confiscated.\n"
"#155.14.4. A Zoltan patrol is not required to explain its motivations to anyone other than Zoltan leadership.\n"
"#155.15.1. Any trading activities leading to the deterioration of the Zoltan economy are forbidden.\n"
"#155.15.2. Transporting alien equipment into Zoltan sectors without clearing customs is forbidden.\n"
"#155.15.3. Transit ships must have a Zoltan representative on board while moving through a Zoltan sector.\n"
"#155.15.4. If no representative is present, ships must move at minimum thrust with weapons and shields disabled.\n"
"#155.15.5. If flight paths intersect, Zoltan ships have priority (in contested cases, the ship with greater mass has priority).\n"
"#155.16.1. Any living organism has a right to life.\n"
"#155.16.1a. Any organism newly discovered by the Zoltan race must be placed in cryostasis in the General Library of Species Preservation.\n"
"#155.16.2. Any organism that violates (or attempts to violate) the right to life of another living organism loses its right to life.\n"
"#155.16.2a. Destruction of another organism in accordance with this code does not deprive the executor of their right to life.\n"
"#155.16.3. Any sentient being has the right to be heard by the Head of the Zoltan Fleet.\n"
"#155.16.4. Within Zoltan sectors, experimentation on sentient beings is forbidden.\n"
"#155.16.5. If a sentient being violates the points of this code, they are reclassified as a NON-sentient organism.\n"
"#155.16.6. Non-sentient organisms are to be registered with a mandatory owner (responsible for their behavior) and only have a right to life.\n"
"#155.16.7. If an organism acts with aggression that threatens others, it may be liquidated.\n"
"#155.16.7a. An organism under mind control is considered not responsible for its actions.\n"
"#155.16.8. Murder or abduction of any Zoltan is punishable by death.\n"
"#155.17.1. Any ship in a Zoltan sector that violates this code must proceed to sector leadership to determine its fate.\n"
"#155.17.2. Upon crossing the border of a Zoltan sector, every ship must identify itself and receive flight clearance.\n"
"#155.17.3. Any ship in a Zoltan sector without official clearance is considered an enemy invader.\n"
"#155.17.4. Analysis or dismantling of any Zoltan equipment is forbidden. To obtain a map of the current sector, press the white button on this device.\n"
"#155.17.5. Scanning of any Zoltan stars, planets, asteroids, ships, stations, projectiles, or wreckage without official permission is forbidden.\n"
"#155.17.6. Any ship with pirate markings is considered an enemy invader.\n"
"#155.17.7. If a pirate crew proves its loyalty to the Zoltans, they will be provided assistance.\n"
"#155.17.8. In critical military situations, the Zoltan fleet must support any ships acting in their military interests (regardless of equipment carried).\n"
"#155.17.8a. Corrective list of technologies permitted in Zoltan sectors (with all accompanying documents): ion weaponry (all classes), beam weaponry (all classes), bomb weaponry (all classes), missile weaponry (power consumption no more than 3 power), Zoltan shield, any Zoltan shield generator, laser weaponry (only small and medium caliber).\n"
"#155.17.8b. Minimum assistance from the Zoltan fleet is 5 fuel cells.\n"
"#155.17.8c. Attempting to doubt the competence of Zoltan leadership is considered deep disrespect and insult. Such behavior toward the Zoltan race is to be eradicated throughout the Galaxy.\n"
"#155.17.8d. If none of a ship's jumps through the Zoltan sector were cleared with the Zoltan race, the ship is considered an enemy invader.\n"
"#END RECORD-155."

